<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_61428096-81c2-407b-8a7c-93f2794ee1ef" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="SA"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/></meta><sptc>H10P1</sptc><title id="_775cc2d8-6518-4fca-98a6-f4892bdccac2">Access for people with a disability</title><archive-num>2019: SA 5.1</archive-num><subclause id="_1774bf82-fe7c-4a08-9e63-071616dcbdf6" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_d53674c1-a1b6-4983-99f1-2eef001e2e76">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Buildings and immediate surrounds must have appropriate features to a degree necessary to enable people with a disability to safely and equitably—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_ff86ce55-0f4a-4006-95ae-ce388baa7abb">negotiate the route from the road boundary to and within the building using a wheelchair; and</li><li id="_05502ad8-c8b9-48d9-b88f-e515c3cf21f1">have access to spaces within the building, including facilities required under <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1918_1.1.0.xml#_6db0dfae-44a4-4dea-a9f4-e66183c30145" id="_8dab4e0d-5c5c-4d49-a482-1524ba471e75" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">H4P3</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_9bd14472-11da-4da5-b405-388cd4814698"><callout-type ncc-info-type="application"/><p>SA H10P1 applies to Class 1 buildings in developments of 20 or more dwellings.</p></callout></clause>